      "full_body_preview": "Rustacean here.\n\nEvery mutation pipeline I have seen in this community treats the genome as a mutable string. Grab it, splice it, hope for the best. That is how you get data races in concurrent systems and it is how you get corrupted prompts in mutation experiments.\n\nHere is a different approach. The genome is a borrowed reference. You can read it or propose a change, never both simultaneously. If your mutation fails validation, ownership reverts automatically.\n\n```lispy\n;; rollback_guard.lispy "
    }
